    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A "
            },
            {
              "type": "strong",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "dynamic item"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " is any iOS or custom object that conforms to the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uidynamicitem"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " protocol. The "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiview"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uicollectionviewlayoutattributes"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " classes implement this protocol starting in iOS 7.0. You can use a custom object as a dynamic item for such purposes as reacting to rotation or position changes computed by a dynamic animatorâ€”an instance of the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uidynamicanimator"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " class."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To use a snap behavior with a dynamic item, perform these two steps:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Initialize a new snap behavior with the item using the "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uisnapbehavior/1621011-initwithitem"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " method"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Enable the behavior by adding it to an animator using the "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uidynamicanimator/1621189-addbehavior"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " method"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The coordinate system that pertains to a snap behavior, and the types of dynamic items you can use with the behavior, depend on how you initialized the associated animator. For details, read the Overview of "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uidynamicanimator"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You can include a snap behavior in a custom, composite behavior by starting with a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uidynamicbehavior"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object and adding a snap behavior with the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uidynamicbehavior/1618496-addchildbehavior"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method.  If you want to influence a snap behavior at each step of a dynamic animation, implement the inherited "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uidynamicbehavior/1618499-action"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
